The paper proposes a new neural network architecture that operates across scale space, which is particularly relevant to computer vision tasks such as image classification and segmentation. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of attention and dynamic routing mechanisms, which are common in natural language processing (NLP) tasks, suggesting that cs.CL (Computation and Language) is another possible sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of residual connections, which are commonly used in deep learning architectures, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the growth of receptive field size with depth, which is relevant to neural network optimization, suggesting that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category as well.
